### Initialize PostHog Provider in Next.js

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog.com/blob/master/contents/tutorials/nextjs-bootstrap-flags.md

Sets up the PostHog provider for a Next.js application. It initializes the PostHog client with the project API key and API host, making feature flags available throughout the application. This script should be placed in a `providers.js` file within the `app` directory.

```javascript
// app/providers.js
'use client'
import posthog from 'posthog-js'
import { PostHogProvider } from 'posthog-js/react'

if (typeof window !== 'undefined') {
  posthog.init("<ph_project_api_key>", {
    api_host: "<ph_client_api_host>"
  })
}
```

