### Initialize PostHog Backend Singleton (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/posthog/posthog.com/blob/master/contents/tutorials/nextjs-error-monitoring.md

Initializes PostHog from `posthog-node` as a singleton for backend use. Requires project API key and host from PostHog settings. The singleton pattern ensures only one instance is created.

```javascript
// app/posthog-server.js
import { PostHog } from 'posthog-node'

let posthogInstance = null

export function getPostHogServer() {
  if (!posthogInstance) {
    posthogInstance = new PostHog(
      '<ph_project_api_key>',
      {
        host: '<ph_client_api_host>',
        flushAt: 1,
        flushInterval: 0
      }
    )
  }
  return posthogInstance
}
```
